      "name": "ASTM F1717 static compression-bending operating envelope — non-cannulated 7.5 mm construct",
      "description": "Axial compressive load range 0–2500 N applied at 10 mm/min crosshead displacement rate; bending moment arm fixed at 50 mm per ASTM F1717 fixture geometry; screw outer diameter 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm; screw length 45–55 mm; construct lordotic angle 5°–15°; cortical bone surrogate (UHMWPE blocks) density 0.94–0.96 g/cm³; ambient temperature 20–25 °C; relative humidity 30–60 %. Validation experiments (N=11) were conducted within this envelope; sparse coverage at the upper bending-moment boundary (>2200 N) is acknowledged."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw — static monotonic loading only",
      "description": "Model applicability is constrained to non-cannulated titanium-alloy pedicle screws with outer diameter 7.0–8.0 mm under quasi-static monotonic compression-bending per ASTM F1717. The model is NOT applicable to: cannulated screw designs, dynamic fatigue loading, screw diameters outside 7.0–8.0 mm, or spinal levels other than thoracolumbar. Material must be Ti-6Al-4V ELI (ASTM F136) or equivalent with yield strength ≥ 795 MPa."
    }
